Gauteng is now the epicentre of the coronavirus pandemic with over 100,000 confirmed cases. Editor's note: This live event has ended. You may watch a recording above. JOHANNESBURG - Gauteng is now the epicentre of the coronavirus pandemic with over 100,000 confirmed cases. The number of infections has exceeded 300,000 nationally. READ: Gauteng Premier tests positive for COVID-19 Gauteng Premier David Makhura and his team delivered an update on COVID-19 in the province. Makhura last week confirmed that he tested positive for COVID-19. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.